dct_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Beograd, sheet Y-17.A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4413)
dct_description_sm: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4413. Alternate title: Beograd. Lambert conical orthomorphic projection. Danube zone grid. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and and spot elevations. With a Serb and Croat glossary. Corrected from intelligence reports up to April 1944. Compiled and drawn by the War Office, 1944. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete. Geographic area is designated as part of Yugoslavia it is now Serbia and Montenegro.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1949.
